g.id: To search for an integer v in an array A of length n: check if A[0] is equal to v if they are equal, return 0 if not, start over again: search for v in the rest of A, i.e. in sub-array [A[1], ..., A[n-1]] if A is empty, return -1

path.id: There are two methods of coding this: use an auxiliary function with an extra argument: start of the array to search use sub-arrays
